50 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
51 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
52 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
53 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
54 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
55 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
56  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
57 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
58 #else
59 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
60 #endif
61 #endif
62 
63 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
64 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
65 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
66 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
67 #else
68 #error "unknown compiler"
69 #endif
70 
71 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
72 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
73 #else
74 #include <cstdio>
75 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
76  do { \
77  fputs(msg, stderr); \
78  DNNL_TRAP(); \
79  } while (0)
80 #endif

96 struct error : public std::exception {
97  dnnl_status_t status;
98  const char *message;
99 
104  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
105  : status(status), message(message) {}
106 
108  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
109 
115  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
116  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
117  }
118 };
119 
121 template <typename T>
122 void validate_container_size(const T &v, const char *error_message,
123  int min_size = 1, int max_size = -1) {
124  const int size = (int)v.size();
125  if (size < min_size || (max_size >= 0 && size > max_size))
126  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, error_message);
127 }
129 
131 template <typename T>
132 struct handle_traits {};
133 
147 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
148 struct handle {
149 private:
150  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
151  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
152 
153 protected:
154  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
155  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
156 
157 public:
165  handle() = default;
166 
168  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
170  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
172  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
174  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
175 
181  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
182 
188  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
189  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
190  }
191 
197  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
198  T result = data_.get();
199  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
200  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
201  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
202  return result;
203  }
204 
209  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
210 
214  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
215 
222  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
223  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
224  }
225 
232  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
233 };

405 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
406  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
407  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
408  // returns a C type.
409  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
410  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
411  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
412  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
413  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
414 }

670 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
671  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
672  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
673  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
674  } \
675 \
676  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
677  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
678  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
679  } \
680 \
681  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
682  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
683  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
684  } \
685 \
686  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
687  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
688  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
689  return lhs; \
690  } \
691 \
692  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
693  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
694  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
695  return lhs; \
696  } \
697 \
698  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
699  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
700  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
701  return lhs; \
702  } \
703 \
704  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
705  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
706  }
707 
708 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
709 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

869 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
870  friend struct primitive;
871  friend struct reorder;
872 
874  enum class kind {
876  any = dnnl_any_engine,
878  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
880  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
881  };
882 
883  using handle::handle;
884 
887  engine() = default;
888 
893  static size_t get_count(kind kind) {
894  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(kind));
895  }
896 
902  engine(kind kind, size_t index) {
903  dnnl_engine_t engine;
904  error::wrap_c_api(
905  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(kind), index),
906  "could not create an engine");
907  reset(engine);
908  }
909 
910 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
911  engine(kind kind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
918  dnnl_engine_t engine;
919  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(
920  &engine, convert_to_c(kind), device, context),
921  "could not create an engine");
922  reset(engine);
923  }
924 #endif
925 
926 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
927  DNNL_API engine(kind akind, const cl::sycl::device &dev,
933  const cl::sycl::context &ctx);
934 #endif
935 
940  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
941  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
942  error::wrap_c_api(
943  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
944  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
945  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
946  reset(c_engine, true);
947  }
948 
951  kind get_kind() const {
952  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
953  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
954  "could not get kind of an engine");
955  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
956  }
957 
958 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
959  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
962  cl_context context = nullptr;
963  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
964  "could not get an OpenCL context fron an engine");
965  return context;
966  }
967 
970  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
971  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
972  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
973  "could not get an OpenCL device fron an engine");
974  return device;
975  }
976 #endif
977 
978 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
979  cl::sycl::context DNNL_API get_sycl_context() const;
981 
983  cl::sycl::device DNNL_API get_sycl_device() const;
984 #endif

991  template <typename primitive_desc>
992  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
993  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
994  }
995 
996 private:
997  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind kind) {
998  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(kind);
999  }
1000 
1001  template <typename primitive_desc>
1002  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
1003  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1004  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1005  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
1006  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1007  return engine(c_engine, true);
1008  }
1009 };

1062 #if DNNL_CPU_THREADING_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_THREADPOOL
1063  void set_threadpool(threadpool_iface *threadpool) {
1071  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_attr_set_threadpool(get(), threadpool),
1072  "could not set stream threadpool attribute");
1073  }
1074 
1080  threadpool_iface *get_threadpool() {
1081  threadpool_iface *tp;
1082  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_attr_get_threadpool(get(), (void **)&tp),
1083  "could not set stream threadpool attribute");
1084  return tp;
1085  }
1086 #endif
1087 };

1090 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1091  using handle::handle;
1092 
1094  enum class flags : unsigned {
1097  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1099  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1101  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1103  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1104  };
1105 
1108  stream() = default;
1109 
1116  stream(const engine &engine, flags flags = flags::default_flags,
1117  const stream_attr &attr = stream_attr()) {
1118  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1119  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_v2(&stream, engine.get(),
1120  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(flags),
1121  attr.get(true)),
1122  "could not create a stream");
1123  reset(stream);
1124  }
1125 
1126 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1127  stream(const engine &engine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1132  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1133  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, engine.get(), queue),
1134  "could not create a stream");
1135  reset(stream);
1136  }
1137 
1140  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1141  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1142  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1143  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1144  return queue;
1145  }
1146 #endif
1147 
1148 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
1149  DNNL_API stream(const engine &eng, cl::sycl::queue &aqueue);
1154 
1156  cl::sycl::queue DNNL_API get_sycl_queue() const;
1157 #endif
1158 
1161  stream &wait() {
1162  error::wrap_c_api(
1163  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1164  return *this;
1165  }
1166 };

1783  struct desc {
1784  friend struct memory;
1786  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1787 
1790  desc() : data() {}
1791 
1807  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1808  format_tag format_tag, bool allow_empty = false)
1809  : data() {
1810  validate_dims(dims);
1811  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
1812  (int)dims.size(), dims.data(), convert_to_c(data_type),
1813  convert_to_c(format_tag));
1814  if (!allow_empty)
1815  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1816  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a "
1817  "format tag");
1818  }
1819 
1835  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1836  const memory::dims &strides, bool allow_empty = false)
1837  : data() {
1838  validate_dims(dims);
1839  if (!strides.empty()) validate_dims(strides, (int)dims.size());
1840  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
1841  (int)dims.size(), dims.data(), convert_to_c(data_type),
1842  strides.empty() ? nullptr : &strides[0]);
1843  if (!allow_empty)
1844  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1845  "could not construct a memory descriptor using "
1846  "strides");
1847  }
1848 
1852  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
1853 
1856  //
1865  desc submemory_desc(const memory::dims &dims,
1866  const memory::dims &offsets, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1867  validate_dims(dims, data.ndims);
1868  validate_dims(offsets, data.ndims);
1869  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1870  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1871  &sub_md, &data, dims.data(), offsets.data());
1872  if (!allow_empty)
1873  error::wrap_c_api(status, "could not construct a sub-memory");
1874  return desc(sub_md);
1875  }
1876 
1921  desc reshape(const memory::dims &dims, bool allow_empty = false) const {
1922  if (data.ndims) validate_dims(dims, 1);
1923  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1924  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(
1925  &out_md, &data, (int)dims.size(), dims.data());
1926  if (!allow_empty)
1927  error::wrap_c_api(
1928  status, "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1929  return desc(out_md);
1930  }
1931 
1968  desc permute_axes(const std::vector<int> &permutation,
1969  bool allow_empty = false) const {
1970  validate_dims(permutation, data.ndims);
1971  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
1972  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_permute_axes(
1973  &out_md, &data, permutation.data());
1974  if (!allow_empty)
1975  error::wrap_c_api(status,
1976  "could not permute axes of a memory descriptor");
1977  return desc(out_md);
1978  }
1979 
1984  memory::dims dims() const {
1985  return memory::dims(data.dims, data.dims + data.ndims);
1986  }
1987 
1990  memory::data_type data_type() const {
1991  return static_cast<memory::data_type>(data.data_type);
1992  }
1993 
1998  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1999 
2003  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
2004 
2009  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
2010  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
2011  }
2012 
2017  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
2018  };
2019 
2020  // Default constructor.
2021  //
2022  // Constructs an empty memory object, which can be used to indicate absence
2023  // of a parameter.
2024  memory() = default;
2025 
2026 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
2027  memory(const desc &md, const engine &engine, void *ahandle)
2033 #ifdef DNNL_USE_DPCPP_USM
2034  : memory(with_sycl_tag {}, md, engine, ahandle, true) {
2035  }
2036 #else
2037  : memory(with_sycl_tag {}, md, engine, ahandle, false) {
2038  }
2039 #endif
2040 #else

2064  dnnl_memory_create(&result, &md.data, engine.get(), handle),
2065  "could not create a memory object");

2067  }
2068 #endif

2229 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL && defined(DNNL_USE_SYCL_BUFFERS)
2230  template <typename T, int ndims = 1>
2235  cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> get_sycl_buffer(size_t *offset = nullptr) const {
2236  static_assert(ndims == 1, "only 1D buffers supported");
2237 
2238  void *handle_ptr;
2239  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_get_data_handle(get(), &handle_ptr),
2240  "could not get SYCL buffer object");
2241 
2242  // XXX: workaround for ComputeCpp
2243  // ComputeCpp fails to construct zero-range buffer
2244  if (!handle_ptr)
2245  return cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims>(cl::sycl::range<1>(1));
2246 
2247  auto &buf_u8 = *static_cast<cl::sycl::buffer<uint8_t, 1> *>(handle_ptr);
2248  if (offset) *offset = 0;
2249  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf_u8.get_size() / sizeof(T));
2250  return buf_u8.reinterpret<T, 1>(range);
2251  }
2252 
2258  template <typename T, int ndims>
2259  void set_sycl_buffer(cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> &buf) {
2260  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf.get_size());
2261  auto buf_u8 = buf.template reinterpret<uint8_t, 1>(range);
2262  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_set_data_handle(
2263  get(), static_cast<void *>(&buf_u8)),
2264  "could not set SYCL buffer object");
2265  }
2266 #endif
2267

2269  return static_cast<dnnl_data_type_t>(data_type);
2270  }

2272  return static_cast<dnnl_format_tag_t>(format);
2273  }

2280  void *ahandle, bool is_usm);
2281 #endif

2972  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2973  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
2974  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
2975  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
2976  query::exec_arg_md};
2977  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
2978  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
2979  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2980  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
2981 
2982  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
2983  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
2984  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
2985  }

3123  dnnl::primitive::kind get_kind() const {
3124  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;

3126  dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
3127  "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3128  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
3129  }
3130 
3131 protected:
3135  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
3136  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
3137  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
3138  "could not clone a primitive descriptor");
3139  reset(new_pd);
3140  }
3141 
3155  primitive_desc_base(
3156  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
3157  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
3158 
3170  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3171  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
3172  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
3173 
3187  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3188  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
3189  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
3190  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
3191  if (pd == nullptr) return;
3192 
3193  dnnl_status_t rc;
3194 
3195  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
3196  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
3197  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
3198 
3199  // Check that primitive kind matches
3200  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
3201  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3202  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
3203  error::wrap_c_api(
3204  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3205  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
3206  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3207  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
3208 
3209  // Check that propagation kind matches
3210  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
3211  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3212  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
3213 
3214  // Something went wrong
3215  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
3216  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3217  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
3218  "descriptor");
3219 
3220  // Everything is fine
3221  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
3222  || (rc == dnnl_success
3223  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
3224  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
3225  reset_with_clone(pd);
3226  return;
3227  }
3228 
3229  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
3230  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3231  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
3232  }
3233 
3234  using base = primitive_desc_base;
3235 };

3387 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
3388  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
3389  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;

3392  c_mems.push_back(s.data);
3393  return c_mems;

3602 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3603  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3604 
3605  primitive_desc() = default;
3606 
3629  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3630  const engine &engine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3631  bool allow_empty = false)
3632  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3633  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3634  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3635  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, engine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3636  if (!allow_empty)
3637  error::wrap_c_api(
3638  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3639  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3640  fetch_impl();
3641  }
3642 
3647  bool next_impl() {
3648  dnnl_status_t status
3649  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3650  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3651  error::wrap_c_api(
3652  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3653  fetch_impl();
3654  return true;
3655  }
3656 
3657 private:
3658  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3659  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3660  void fetch_impl() {
3661  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3662  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3663  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3664  : dnnl_runtime_error,
3665  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3666  "descriptor iterator");
3667  reset(pd);
3668  }
3669 };

6433  &p),
6434  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive "
6435  "descriptor for batch normalization forward propagation "

6438  : query::dst_md,
6439  kind);
6440  }

7573  }

7577  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_c_desc() const {
7578  return base::query_md(query::exec_arg_md, DNNL_ARG_DIFF_DST_ITER_C);
7579  }
7580 
7581 protected:
7582  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
7583 
7584  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7585  //
7586  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7587  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7588  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7589  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7590  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7591  //
7592  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7593  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7594  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7595  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7596  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7597  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7598  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7599  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7600  dnnl_status_t rc;
7601  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7602  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7603  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7604  "for an RNN primitive");
7605 
7606  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7607  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7608  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7609 
7610  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7611  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7612  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7613  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7614 
7615  if (!ok)
7616  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7617  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7618  "RNN primitive");
7619 
7620  reset_with_clone(pd);
7621  }
7622 };
7623 
7625 struct vanilla_rnn_forward : public primitive {
7627  struct desc {

7629

10278  //

10288  const memory::desc &src_desc, const memory::desc &dst_desc) {

10320 
10333  //
10343  desc(prop_kind prop_kind, algorithm algorithm,
10344  const std::vector<float> &factors, const memory::desc &src_desc,
10345  const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
10346  if (!factors.empty())
10347  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10348  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10349  dnnl::convert_to_c(prop_kind),
10350  convert_to_c(algorithm), factors.data(),
10351  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
10352  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10353  }
10354  };

10708 inline void primitive::execute(const stream &stream,
10709  const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
10710  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
10711  c_args.reserve(args.size());
10712  for (const auto &a : args)
10713  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
10714 
10715  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), stream.get(),
10716  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
10717  "could not execute a primitive");
10718 }
